# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Task Reference
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Task types:
#   Shell    - Run a shell command (cmd, shell, literal, path)
#   Script   - Run a script file (path, runner)
#   HTTP     - Download a file (url, dest)
#   Wait     - Poll until ready (url [http or tcp host:port], timeout)
#   Template - Render a file with $VAR substitution (src, dest)
#   Group    - Run a named task group (ref, parallel, attempts, delay)
#   Git      - Git operation (op: pull|checkout|fetch|reset, branch, path)
#   Prompt   - Ask the user for input (var, message, default)
#   Confirm  - Ask for yes/no confirmation (message)
#   Set      - Set an environment variable (var, value)
#   Print    - Print a message (message, color, literal)
#
# Common task options:
#   concurrent - Run this task in parallel with the next tasks (true/false)
#   condition  - Only run if all conditions are met:
#     platform - darwin (mac), linux, or windows
#     exists   - file or directory path that must exist
#     cmd      - shell command that must exit 0
